    <para id="para-00028">If your company uses leverage, raising $7,000 of financing by issuing debt with a 4% interest rate, it will have an interest expense of $280. This lowers its taxable income to $51,720 and its taxes to $14,481.60. Because interest is a tax-deductible expense, using leverage lowers the company’s taxes.</para>
    <para id="para-00029"><link target-id="table-00003" document="m00109"/> shows that the company’s net income is lower with leverage than it would be without leverage. In other words, debt obligations will reduce the value of the equity. However, less equity is needed because some of the firm is financed through debt. The important consideration is how the use of leverage changes the total amount of dollars available to all investors. <link target-id="table-00003" document="m00109"/> shows this impact.</para>
    <table summary="Some cells are left blank for visual design purposes." id="table-00003">
    <title>Total Dollars Available to Investors</title>
    <tgroup cols="3">
    <colspec colnum="1" colname="c1"/>
    <colspec colnum="2" colname="c2"/>
    <colspec colnum="3" colname="c3"/>
    <thead>
      <row>
    <entry align="center"> </entry>
    <entry align="center">Without Leverage</entry>
    <entry align="center">With Leverage</entry>
  </row>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
    <row>
    <entry>Interest Paid to Debt Holders</entry>
    <entry align="right">$0.00</entry>
    <entry align="right">$280.00</entry>
    </row>
    <row>
    <entry>Amount Available to Stockholders</entry>
    <entry align="right"><emphasis effect="underline">37,440.00</emphasis></entry>
    <entry align="right"><emphasis effect="underline">37,238.40</emphasis></entry>
    </row>
    <row>
    <entry><emphasis effect="bold">Total Available for All Investors</emphasis><emphasis effect="bold"> </emphasis></entry>
    <entry align="right"><emphasis effect="bold"><emphasis effect="underline">$37,440.00</emphasis></emphasis><emphasis effect="bold"><emphasis effect="underline"> </emphasis></emphasis></entry>
    <entry align="right"><emphasis effect="bold"><emphasis effect="underline">$37,518.40</emphasis></emphasis><emphasis effect="bold"><emphasis effect="underline"> </emphasis></emphasis></entry>
