    <glossary>
    <definition id="def-00001"><term>interest tax shield</term><meaning>the reduction in taxes paid because interest payments on debt are a tax-deductible expense; calculated as the corporate tax rate multiplied by interest payments</meaning></definition>
    <definition id="def-00002"><term>levered equity</term><meaning>equity in a firm that has debt outstanding</meaning></definition>
    <definition id="def-00003"><term>unlevered equity</term><meaning>equity in a firm that has no debt outstanding</meaning></definition>
    </glossary>
